  • Daily Reliability: 69.6% daily riders need consistent, glanceable interface

Step 8B: User Experience Preferences

Dashboard Element Usage Patterns

Key Finding: Among riders with digital dashboards, the most frequently checked elements provide clear priorities for dashboard design.

Top 5 Most Checked Elements:

  • Speed: 172 riders (88.7%)
  • Battery/Fuel: 166 riders (85.6%)
  • Navigation: 82 riders (42.3%)
  • Range: 79 riders (40.7%)
  • Time: 71 riders (36.6%)

Insight: These elements should have the highest visibility and easiest access in any dashboard redesign.

Valued Design Qualities

Key Finding: Riders prioritize specific emotional and functional qualities in dashboard design.

Top 3 Valued Qualities:

  • Simplicity: 121 riders (62.4%)
  • Trustworthy: 86 riders (44.3%)
  • Minimalist: 64 riders (33.0%)

Insight: Design should emphasize simplicity and trustworthiness while maintaining a clean, minimalist aesthetic.

Interface Interaction Preferences

Key Finding: Riders have varied preferences for dashboard interaction methods.

Interaction Method Distribution:

  • Both: 94 riders (48.5%)
  • Button: 65 riders (33.5%)
  • Touch: 51 riders (26.3%)
  • Voice control: 32 riders (16.5%)

Insight: Hybrid approach supporting both touch and button controls would satisfy the majority of users.

Adaptive Dashboard Interest

Key Finding: Strong preference for personalization and adaptive features.

Personalization Demand:

  • Yes (Want Adaptive Dashboard): 92 riders (47.4%)
  • No: 19 riders (9.8%)

Insight: Vast majority wants dashboards that learn and adapt to their riding habits - strong case for AI/ML integration.
